# Use the formula Celsius=(Fahrenheit-32)x5/9 to convert several temperature values from Fahrenheit to Celsius.
# Note, each time, you must store the temperature in Fahrenheit in a variable 
# and then use the above formula to calculate its value in Celsius and print the value out.

fahrenheit = 98.6
celsius = ((fahrenheit-32)*5) / 9
print("Fahrenheit", fahrenheit)
print ("Celsius", celsius)

